<TITLE> Chess coach Igor due Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 22 (bdnews24.com) - Latvian GM Igor Rausis is scheduled to arrive in the city Sunday night to conduct a four-moth training camp for top Bangladesh chess players. GM Ziaur Rahman, to represent Bangladesh in the World Chess Championship in Siberia, November-December 2007, will gear up under the supervision of Rausis, who will also look after another eight to nine top players. It would be for the third time that Rausis would train the Bangladesh players. The GM first came in 2000 to guide Bangladesh's Olympiad squad. He also coached Bangladesh in 2002 for the Olympiad. 
